## 🔧 Installation Guide

### 📦 Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/FiloSegGUI.git
cd FiloSegGUI
🐍 Step 2: Create a Conda Environment (Recommended)
Use Python 3.8.5 — this is the most compatible version for Omnipose + GUI.

bash
Copy
Edit
conda create -n filoseg python=3.8.5
conda activate filoseg
🔥 Step 3: Install PyTorch
If you have a GPU:

bash
Copy
Edit
conda install pytorch torchvision pytorch-cuda=11.8 -c pytorch -c nvidia
If you’re using CPU only:

bash
Copy
Edit
conda install pytorch torchvision cpuonly -c pytorch
✅ Step 4: Install Python Requirements
bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
This includes:

Omnipose (older stable commit)

GUI libraries (PySide6, tifffile, matplotlib, etc.)

Torch, NumPy, Pillow

🚀 Run the GUI
bash
Copy
Edit
python main.py
📂 Pretrained Models
All pretrained models should be placed in the FiloGUI_models/ directory. This includes:

Coni_4.pth

FilaTip_6.pth

Retrain_omni_4.pth

... and others

The models are referenced using relative paths like:

python
Copy
Edit
"./FiloGUI_models/Coni_4.pth"
✅ Pro Tip: You can upload only small .pth examples and link to larger ones using GitHub Releases or Google Drive.

🧪 Retraining Models
To retrain:

Go to the "Retrain" tab.

Choose a folder of images and select the corresponding mask suffix (_cp_masks by default).

Select a pretrained .pth model as your base.

Start training — the model will be saved in the models/ subfolder.

🧠 Dependencies
Python 3.8.5

PyTorch 2.5.1

Omnipose (commit 04b09e7)

PySide6 6.9.0

numpy, pillow, matplotlib, tifffile, natsort

🛠 Troubleshooting
If you see an error like:

vbnet
Copy
Edit
cellpose not found. Error: The 'cellpose' distribution was not found
Install Cellpose CLI manually:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install cellpose
